<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04871</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR SECURITY OF TENURE FOR ALL CASUAL AND CONTRACTUAL EMPLOYEES OF THE GOVERNMENT WHO HAVE RENDERED THE PRESCRIBED YEARS OF SERVICE IN THE NATIONAL GOVERNMENT AGENCIES AND THE LOCAL GOVERNMENT UNITS AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates that all incumbent casual and contractual government employees who have rendered at least 5 years of continuous service in the case of national government agencies or a total of 10 years of continuous service in the case of local government units, shall be entitled to security of tenure subject to certain conditions.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VARGAS, ALFRED D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-01-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Bravo (M.) (088 2017-05-10)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2017-02-06</td></tr></table>